Preparations are complete for Steve Fossett's solo, non-stop flight around the globe aboard the GlobalFlyer.
The main challenge is avoiding the turbulent jet stream until reaching a cruising altitude of 45,000 feet.
Fossett, equipped with a parachute, is ready for the three-day journey testing his endurance and piloting skills.
Despite GPS malfunctions and antenna issues, Fossett remains optimistic.
The project, funded by Virgin Atlantic, aims to inspire interest in aviation and advance fuel-efficient aircraft technology.
